jobInfo.postDescription:
Educational Background
-	Electrical Information technology, Computer, Communication or related profession bachelor degree with min 2 years of work experience
Technical Skills
-	Strong C or C++ programming experience
-	Familiar with CANoe software
-	Min 2 years experience in embedded software development
-	Knowledge of micro-controller hardware and peripherals
-	Knowledge of automotive networks (CAN, LIN, K-Line)
-	Experience in software module and integration testing
-	Experience in LabWindows / VC++ / VB/Python is considered as an advantage
Language Skills
-	College English Test Band 4 (CET 4)
-	College English Test Band 6(CET 6) preferred

IT Skills


Soft Skill
-	Ability to work autonomously in an international environment creativity, team spirit and a pro-active attitude are imperative
-	Good self-study ability
-	Good communication skill
Essential responsibilities
-	Development of real time software for automotive electronics systems.
-	Development of software for computer based applications. 
-	Develop software concepts, perform software design and implement design for low level hardware interface software and modular application software
-	Coding in C,C++ or Python language.
-	Conduct document and code reviews
-	Support implementation of algorithms
-	Conduct module tests and software integration tests and support system integration tests.
